- #references

    - FACIT PD: a framework for analysis and creation of intergenerational techniques for participatory design

    - Meta

        - Authored by::  [[Greg Walsh]] ,  Elizabeth Foss ,  [[Jason Yip]] ,  [[Allison Druin]]

        - Year: 2013

        - Publication: CHI '13

    - #lit-context:

        - Kidsteam @ UMD (an intergenerational design team) and using various methods and techniques in PD and co-design

    - #[[üìù lit-notes]]

        - FACIT PD Framework with 8 dimensions:

        - ![](data:image/png;base64,)

            - "PD is an overarching methodology" and "co-design" is a subset of PD (p. 2893)

            - Differentiating between method and methodology

                - "Cooperative Inquiry, Bonded Design, and Informant Design are examples of popular methods used in the intergenerational co-design process" (p. 2894)

        - ![](data:image/png;base64,)

            - Muller and Kuhn, Sanders cited

            - Methods vs techniques (p. 2894)

            - Provides overview of Cooperative Inquiry, Informant Design, and Bonded Design

            - MESS day method and Bluebells methods focused on playfulness

            - Aim: to "create a framework for developing new techniques to support intergenerational PD" (p. 2895)

        - ![](data:image/png;base64,)

            - Techniques include:

                - Bags of Stuff --> which can be modified to "Mobile Bags of Stuff" (p. 2895)

                - Storyboarding

                - Stickies

                - Paper prototyping

                - Big paper

                - KidReporter

                - Mixing Ideas

                - Comicboarding

                - Mission from Mars

                - Layored Elaboration

                - Obstructed Theater

            - FACIT PD:

        - ![](data:image/png;base64,)

            - 1. **Partner Experience** (p. 2896)

                - refers to how much design experience is necessary to participate in the design session

                - less experience warrants comicboarding, more experience warrants bags of stuff techniques or more collaborative techniques

                - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2Fzv2sG7GbBM?alt=media&token=d589ed2f-0566-4df5-807f-a6034d5f4f8b)

            - 2. **Need for accommodation** (p. 2897) #barrier

                - refers to the age and cognitive ability of the design partner

                - "Partners with special needs may need additional supports as well, such as ensuring that there is a complete supportive team in place" #barrier

                - "some partners may need to dictate their drawings to a proxy artist" and "any other member of the design team could act as the proxy" #barrier

                - some partners may have social issues and working in a group may not be ideal #barrier

                - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2F-I7DAa_yqy?alt=media&token=c7bb7b6c-6cd6-4186-9402-8663cb8ef920)

            - **3. Design Space**

                - looks at how specifically the design problem is defined (p. 2897)

            - 4. **Maturity of the Design**

                - looks at how far along the current design is in the overall design process

            - **5. Cost**

                - refers to the financial price of materials required for the technique

                - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FvObsXhFDju?alt=media&token=8cc37982-b59a-4e3f-8848-cd9c790b00ae)

            - 6.** Portability**

                - refers to physical mobility of technique or the artifacts generated by the techniques

                - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FuRomFueJ6c?alt=media&token=06ca55dc-7da2-4301-b9a9-90272f4105b6)

            - 7. **Technology Level**

                - looks at sophistication of technology used in the technique (p. 2898)

            - 8. **Physical Interaction** #barrier (design is messy process that necessitates movement of people and things?)

                - looks at how much design partners will physically move around during the design process because of the technique (p. 2898)

        - ![](data:image/png;base64,)

            - Comicboarding design challenges

            - Mission from mars design challenges

            - Creating new techniques using FACIT PD: (p. 2899)

                - Big Props to be used with motion-based technology

                - Line judging

                - Team Construction

            - "in each technique, changes to dimensions need to be thought of as trade-offs" (p. 2901)

                - e.g. higher physical interaction most likely means lower portability

            - FACIT PD complements Sanders' framework from 2010 PDC paper (READ NEXT!)

            - Future work:

                - underserved populations of children

                - does FACIT PD hold for adults?

        - My reactions/thoughts: Perhaps we don't need more tools/techniques, we need frameworks to point people to which tools/techniques they should use

    - #observation-notes

        - Design space, maturity of design, cost, portability, technolgy dimension and physical interaction all work on a [sliding scale](![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FpnYxRHTII3.png?alt=media&token=ef3efd2c-eff5-46d6-bcb8-67f0d1e79748) pg 2898 ) depending upon the needs of the project.

            - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FpnYxRHTII3.png?alt=media&token=ef3efd2c-eff5-46d6-bcb8-67f0d1e79748) pg 2898

        - Techniques should be developed which [maximize child engagement and allow for effective communication](![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FpgG-i5nBVB.png?alt=media&token=cf5c0d36-16f8-4b2d-b392-91c8a0f853b4) pg 2901) between children and adults.

            - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FpgG-i5nBVB.png?alt=media&token=cf5c0d36-16f8-4b2d-b392-91c8a0f853b4) pg 2901

        - Techniques should be altered and developed based on the needs of the project to maximize its efficiency.

            - ![](https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/firescript-577a2.appspot.com/o/imgs%2Fapp%2Fmegacoglab%2FVTpzymdM3o.png?alt=media&token=3afa8876-2e60-4b46-8acb-ddf03a377888) pg 2901
